# Server & API layer

## Split

| Location | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| `app/server/{domain}.ts` | `createServerFn` — validate input, call lib, return DTO |
| `app/lib/server/{domain}.ts` | Business logic, DB, OAuth, encryption |
| `app/lib/*-schemas.ts` | Zod input/output schemas (shared client + server) |
| `app/lib/bootstrap-query.ts`, `app/lib/query.ts` | React Query options wrapping server fns |

## Rules

- One domain per server file (`dashboard.ts`, `setup.ts`, `projects.ts`, `channels.ts`).
- Never define the same server fn in a route file.
- OAuth token exchange, PKCE, profile fetch → `app/lib/server/oauth/`.
- DB access → `app/lib/server/` or `app/lib/db/repository.ts`; not in components.

## Client usage

```tsx
// Hook server fn once at component top
const saveFn = useServerFn(saveProject)
// Or use queryOptions from app/lib/*-query.ts
```

Do not inline `fetch()` to internal APIs when a server fn exists.
